WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.984 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.984 --> 00:00:06.480 align:middle line:90%


00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:07.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you all.

00:00:07.420 --> 00:00:09.990 align:middle line:84%
Thank you all for coming so
early on a Sunday morning.

00:00:09.990 --> 00:00:13.130 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.130 --> 00:00:16.680 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a morning person, so
I'm so grateful to all of you

00:00:16.680 --> 00:00:18.640 align:middle line:90%
for being here.

00:00:18.640 --> 00:00:21.360 align:middle line:84%
How many of you
have never heard me

00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:28.740 align:middle line:84%
speak before, not read my
book, not seen my TED Talk?

00:00:28.740 --> 00:00:31.360 align:middle line:84%
OK, how many have never
heard me speak live before?

00:00:31.360 --> 00:00:32.520 align:middle line:90%
OK, quite a few.

00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:33.960 align:middle line:90%
Great.

00:00:33.960 --> 00:00:36.590 align:middle line:84%
That means I get to use the same
old jokes, and you'll laugh.

00:00:36.590 --> 00:00:37.390 align:middle line:90%
Yay.

00:00:37.390 --> 00:00:42.350 align:middle line:90%


00:00:42.350 --> 00:00:47.460 align:middle line:84%
I am so happy to be
here, happy to be here

00:00:47.460 --> 00:00:49.910 align:middle line:90%
in this room with all of you--

00:00:49.910 --> 00:00:54.640 align:middle line:84%
with all of you beautiful
people, beautiful souls.

00:00:54.640 --> 00:01:01.810 align:middle line:84%
But I'm also happy to be alive
here on this physical Earth,

00:01:01.810 --> 00:01:06.880 align:middle line:84%
because if the doctors were
right, the last day of my life

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:12.310 align:middle line:84%
should have been
February the 2nd, 2006.

00:01:12.310 --> 00:01:14.580 align:middle line:90%
That was 13 years ago.

00:01:14.580 --> 00:01:19.070 align:middle line:84%
13 years ago, I should
have left this planet.

00:01:19.070 --> 00:01:21.140 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sort of here
on borrowed time.

00:01:21.140 --> 00:01:27.440 align:middle line:84%
But on that day on
February the 2nd, 2006,

00:01:27.440 --> 00:01:30.710 align:middle line:90%
I had end-stage lymphoma--

00:01:30.710 --> 00:01:31.670 align:middle line:90%
end-stage cancer.

00:01:31.670 --> 00:01:35.670 align:middle line:90%


00:01:35.670 --> 00:01:38.160 align:middle line:84%
I had cancer for
four years, which

00:01:38.160 --> 00:01:42.000 align:middle line:84%
had spread and metastasized
all over my body.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:45.300 align:middle line:84%
It started with a
lump on my neck.

00:01:45.300 --> 00:01:48.750 align:middle line:84%
And over a period of
four years, it spread.

00:01:48.750 --> 00:01:52.950 align:middle line:84%
It started with a
diagnosis of stage 2.

00:01:52.950 --> 00:01:57.060 align:middle line:84%
And then it continued to
spread into my breasts and all

00:01:57.060 --> 00:01:58.800 align:middle line:90%
around my neck.

00:01:58.800 --> 00:02:05.740 align:middle line:84%
And by 2006, four years
on, I had tumors--

00:02:05.740 --> 00:02:08.710 align:middle line:84%
many of them the
size of golf balls--

00:02:08.710 --> 00:02:14.680 align:middle line:84%
from the base of my skull, all
around my neck, under my arms,

00:02:14.680 --> 00:02:19.510 align:middle line:84%
and in my breasts, all the
way down to my abdomen.

00:02:19.510 --> 00:02:25.240 align:middle line:84%
By that point, the doctors had
given me three months to live.

00:02:25.240 --> 00:02:32.640 align:middle line:84%
And at that time, my body had
stopped absorbing nutrition.

00:02:32.640 --> 00:02:34.230 align:middle line:90%
I had lost so much weight.

00:02:34.230 --> 00:02:38.130 align:middle line:84%
I weighed between
80 to 85 pounds.

00:02:38.130 --> 00:02:42.060 align:middle line:84%
My muscles had
completely deteriorated.

00:02:42.060 --> 00:02:46.020 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't even have
the strength to stand.

00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:48.270 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't even hold my head up.

00:02:48.270 --> 00:02:51.930 align:middle line:84%
My head would be
hanging down on my neck.

00:02:51.930 --> 00:02:55.950 align:middle line:84%
My neck didn't have the
strength to hold my head up.

00:02:55.950 --> 00:02:59.700 align:middle line:84%
My lungs would fill with
fluid and had to be drained

00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:01.560 align:middle line:90%
frequently, regularly.

00:03:01.560 --> 00:03:04.420 align:middle line:90%


00:03:04.420 --> 00:03:09.490 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't lie down flat, or
I would choke on my own fluid.

00:03:09.490 --> 00:03:14.160 align:middle line:84%
I breathed with the
aid of an oxygen tank.

00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:16.960 align:middle line:84%
I had an oxygen mask on
my face all the time.

00:03:16.960 --> 00:03:20.400 align:middle line:90%


00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:24.250 align:middle line:90%
I had open skin lesions.

00:03:24.250 --> 00:03:30.780 align:middle line:84%
And on February the 2nd,
2006, my organs shut down.

00:03:30.780 --> 00:03:35.640 align:middle line:84%
I had been in so much pain up
until that point and so much

00:03:35.640 --> 00:03:43.530 align:middle line:84%
discomfort, because I couldn't
walk, I couldn't sleep,

00:03:43.530 --> 00:03:45.720 align:middle line:84%
because I would choke
on my own fluid.

00:03:45.720 --> 00:03:48.880 align:middle line:84%
So I had to be propped
up all the time.

00:03:48.880 --> 00:03:53.010 align:middle line:84%
And I'd been in so much pain
and so much discomfort--

00:03:53.010 --> 00:03:56.770 align:middle line:84%
and I even remember that on
the night of February the 1st,

00:03:56.770 --> 00:04:00.180 align:middle line:84%
the nurse gave me an
extra shot of morphine,

00:04:00.180 --> 00:04:02.110 align:middle line:84%
just so that I'd
be able to sleep.

00:04:02.110 --> 00:04:04.500 align:middle line:90%
I was so tired.

00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:06.520 align:middle line:90%
I was just so tired.

00:04:06.520 --> 00:04:09.060 align:middle line:90%
I had been fighting for my life.

00:04:09.060 --> 00:04:11.610 align:middle line:84%
I had been fighting
to stay alive.

00:04:11.610 --> 00:04:15.330 align:middle line:84%
Up until that point, I felt
I had tried everything,

00:04:15.330 --> 00:04:18.510 align:middle line:84%
and I mean everything,
to stay alive.

00:04:18.510 --> 00:04:22.710 align:middle line:84%
And finally, on February
the 1st, I let go.

00:04:22.710 --> 00:04:23.910 align:middle line:90%
I stopped fighting.

00:04:23.910 --> 00:04:24.810 align:middle line:90%
I was done.

00:04:24.810 --> 00:04:26.390 align:middle line:90%
I was just done.

00:04:26.390 --> 00:04:31.530 align:middle line:84%
And on the morning of February
the 2nd, I didn't wake up.

00:04:31.530 --> 00:04:36.000 align:middle line:84%
And my husband, who was frantic,
was calling the doctors.

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.140 align:middle line:84%
And the doctors said that
my organs had now shut down,

00:04:40.140 --> 00:04:43.560 align:middle line:84%
and these were my final
hours, and that I was not

00:04:43.560 --> 00:04:45.270 align:middle line:90%
going to come out of the coma.

00:04:45.270 --> 00:04:47.340 align:middle line:90%
I had gone into a coma.

00:04:47.340 --> 00:04:49.260 align:middle line:84%
And the doctors informed
him that I was not

00:04:49.260 --> 00:04:51.780 align:middle line:90%
going to come out of the coma.

00:04:51.780 --> 00:04:52.950 align:middle line:90%
My mom was there.

00:04:52.950 --> 00:04:56.680 align:middle line:84%
She was there because I had
been getting sicker and sicker.

00:04:56.680 --> 00:04:59.100 align:middle line:84%
They had been contemplating
calling my brother, who

00:04:59.100 --> 00:05:00.660 align:middle line:90%
was in a different country.

00:05:00.660 --> 00:05:03.420 align:middle line:84%
This was happening
to me in Hong Kong.

00:05:03.420 --> 00:05:06.150 align:middle line:84%
And they were contemplating
calling my brother, who

00:05:06.150 --> 00:05:08.280 align:middle line:90%
was in India at the time.

00:05:08.280 --> 00:05:11.310 align:middle line:84%
And up until that point,
I kept saying to them,

00:05:11.310 --> 00:05:15.420 align:middle line:84%
don't concern him, don't worry
him, he's got his family.

00:05:15.420 --> 00:05:18.750 align:middle line:84%
But the interesting thing is,
when I went into the coma,

00:05:18.750 --> 00:05:22.140 align:middle line:84%
he sensed something before he
even got a call from anyone

00:05:22.140 --> 00:05:23.850 align:middle line:90%
in my family.

00:05:23.850 --> 00:05:25.710 align:middle line:90%
He just felt he had to be here.

00:05:25.710 --> 00:05:28.440 align:middle line:84%
And he went to the
airport to get a ticket.

00:05:28.440 --> 00:05:33.050 align:middle line:84%
And he was already flying
on his way to see me.

00:05:33.050 --> 00:05:37.640 align:middle line:84%
While I was in the coma,
unbeknownst to everyone

00:05:37.640 --> 00:05:43.160 align:middle line:84%
around me, I had
actually left my body.

00:05:43.160 --> 00:05:48.690 align:middle line:84%
And for the first time,
all the pain was gone.

00:05:48.690 --> 00:05:51.270 align:middle line:10%
And the fear was gone.

00:05:51.270 --> 00:05:54.390 align:middle line:90%
And I felt incredible.

00:05:54.390 --> 00:05:57.210 align:middle line:84%
I was aware that my physical
body was lying there

00:05:57.210 --> 00:05:58.980 align:middle line:90%
in that hospital bed.

00:05:58.980 --> 00:06:06.120 align:middle line:84%
But I felt so free and
magnificent and powerful.

00:06:06.120 --> 00:06:11.340 align:middle line:84%
I felt so expanded and
powerful that my physical body

00:06:11.340 --> 00:06:15.900 align:middle line:84%
looked so small and
insignificant compared

00:06:15.900 --> 00:06:19.110 align:middle line:90%
to how I was now feeling.

00:06:19.110 --> 00:06:23.810 align:middle line:84%
I was aware that my
family was distraught.

00:06:23.810 --> 00:06:26.612 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted them to
know that I was OK.

00:06:26.612 --> 00:06:27.820 align:middle line:90%
I really wanted them to know.

00:06:27.820 --> 00:06:30.340 align:middle line:84%
But there was no way for me
to communicate with them.

00:06:30.340 --> 00:06:33.650 align:middle line:90%


00:06:33.650 --> 00:06:36.170 align:middle line:90%
My physical eyes were closed.

00:06:36.170 --> 00:06:38.720 align:middle line:84%
And even though my
physical eyes were closed,

00:06:38.720 --> 00:06:40.880 align:middle line:84%
I was aware of
everything that was

00:06:40.880 --> 00:06:43.440 align:middle line:90%
happening all around the room.

00:06:43.440 --> 00:06:45.590 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't like using
your physical eyes,

00:06:45.590 --> 00:06:48.270 align:middle line:84%
where you have to kind of
turn your head and focus.

00:06:48.270 --> 00:06:52.700 align:middle line:84%
It was more like a
360-degree peripheral vision,

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:54.920 align:middle line:84%
where I was just
aware of everything.

00:06:54.920 --> 00:06:57.950 align:middle line:84%
But I wasn't able to
communicate with my family.

00:06:57.950 --> 00:07:02.220 align:middle line:84%
But I could feel what
they were feeling.

00:07:02.220 --> 00:07:05.100 align:middle line:84%
And yet, I had this
feeling-- even though I

00:07:05.100 --> 00:07:07.380 align:middle line:84%
could see that they
were distraught,

00:07:07.380 --> 00:07:09.510 align:middle line:84%
I had this feeling
that everything's

00:07:09.510 --> 00:07:13.380 align:middle line:90%
going to be OK, even if I died.

00:07:13.380 --> 00:07:15.490 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know that I
was going to come back.

00:07:15.490 --> 00:07:17.660 align:middle line:84%
But there was just this
feeling that everything

00:07:17.660 --> 00:07:19.830 align:middle line:90%
is going to be OK.

00:07:19.830 --> 00:07:22.410 align:middle line:90%
Even if I die, it's OK.

00:07:22.410 --> 00:07:24.420 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:07:24.420 --> 00:07:32.760 align:middle line:84%
And I could feel myself continue
to expand as if I was just--

00:07:32.760 --> 00:07:35.880 align:middle line:84%
I call it just
pure consciousness.

00:07:35.880 --> 00:07:38.020 align:middle line:90%
And I continued to expand.

00:07:38.020 --> 00:07:40.630 align:middle line:84%
And I was aware
that I was dying.

00:07:40.630 --> 00:07:43.140 align:middle line:90%
But it just felt so beautiful.

00:07:43.140 --> 00:07:50.160 align:middle line:84%
I felt as though I was
enveloped in a feeling of just

00:07:50.160 --> 00:07:53.750 align:middle line:90%
pure, unconditional love.

00:07:53.750 --> 00:07:57.660 align:middle line:84%
And I call it "unconditional,"
because actually, there

00:07:57.660 --> 00:08:00.210 align:middle line:84%
is no other kind of love
except unconditional,

00:08:00.210 --> 00:08:02.820 align:middle line:84%
because if it's
not unconditional--

00:08:02.820 --> 00:08:05.610 align:middle line:84%
if it's conditional,
then it's not love.

00:08:05.610 --> 00:08:08.237 align:middle line:84%
As soon as love is conditional,
it's not love anymore.

00:08:08.237 --> 00:08:09.070 align:middle line:90%
It's something else.

00:08:09.070 --> 00:08:10.620 align:middle line:90%
It's approval.

00:08:10.620 --> 00:08:13.620 align:middle line:84%
It's like seeking approval,
which is conditional.

00:08:13.620 --> 00:08:16.230 align:middle line:84%
So what I felt there
was nothing like I

00:08:16.230 --> 00:08:18.690 align:middle line:84%
had ever felt in my
physical life before.

00:08:18.690 --> 00:08:22.170 align:middle line:84%
That was the first time
I had that comparison--

00:08:22.170 --> 00:08:25.200 align:middle line:84%
that oh, my god, all the things
I thought that were love over

00:08:25.200 --> 00:08:26.378 align:middle line:90%
here, were not.

00:08:26.378 --> 00:08:28.170 align:middle line:84%
It was just me seeking
approval and needing

00:08:28.170 --> 00:08:32.159 align:middle line:84%
to behave a certain way
to get people to love me

00:08:32.159 --> 00:08:33.539 align:middle line:90%
or to approve of me.

00:08:33.539 --> 00:08:39.380 align:middle line:84%
I felt I was loved,
regardless of who I was

00:08:39.380 --> 00:08:41.909 align:middle line:90%
or what I had done in my life.

00:08:41.909 --> 00:08:44.270 align:middle line:90%
There was no judgment.

00:08:44.270 --> 00:08:46.280 align:middle line:90%
There was no hell.

00:08:46.280 --> 00:08:50.870 align:middle line:84%
As much as many people here
like to believe there is,

00:08:50.870 --> 00:08:56.750 align:middle line:84%
unfortunately, I can be
certain that there was no hell.

00:08:56.750 --> 00:09:01.560 align:middle line:84%
And there was what I call
a state of clarity, where I

00:09:01.560 --> 00:09:05.310 align:middle line:90%
felt that I understood my life.

00:09:05.310 --> 00:09:08.640 align:middle line:84%
I understood why I had
done everything I had done.

00:09:08.640 --> 00:09:12.220 align:middle line:90%
I understood why I got cancer.

00:09:12.220 --> 00:09:17.170 align:middle line:84%
And basically, you get
to review your own life.

00:09:17.170 --> 00:09:23.320 align:middle line:84%
And you get to, not
in a judgmental way,

00:09:23.320 --> 00:09:26.400 align:middle line:84%
but in a very
compassionate way, you even

00:09:26.400 --> 00:09:28.650 align:middle line:84%
get to review the things
you've done wrong,

00:09:28.650 --> 00:09:30.510 align:middle line:90%
where you've hurt other people.

00:09:30.510 --> 00:09:32.900 align:middle line:84%
And you understand
why you did them.

00:09:32.900 --> 00:09:35.570 align:middle line:90%


00:09:35.570 --> 00:09:37.640 align:middle line:84%
It was just such an
incredible space,

00:09:37.640 --> 00:09:40.325 align:middle line:84%
where I even understood
why I had the cancer.

00:09:40.325 --> 00:09:43.460 align:middle line:90%


00:09:43.460 --> 00:09:47.220 align:middle line:84%
At this point, I could
sense the presence

00:09:47.220 --> 00:09:50.160 align:middle line:84%
of other entities,
which is where

00:09:50.160 --> 00:09:52.800 align:middle line:90%
the love was emanating from.

00:09:52.800 --> 00:09:55.800 align:middle line:84%
It felt like I was just
bathed in this love.

00:09:55.800 --> 00:09:58.470 align:middle line:84%
And I think also
what contributes

00:09:58.470 --> 00:10:02.550 align:middle line:84%
to this feeling of love was that
there's no fear in that realm.

00:10:02.550 --> 00:10:07.800 align:middle line:84%
It made me realize how fearful
we are here in the physical.

00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:09.180 align:middle line:90%
And we don't need to be.

00:10:09.180 --> 00:10:10.980 align:middle line:90%
We really don't need to be.

00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:13.290 align:middle line:84%
But it made me realize
that we are all

00:10:13.290 --> 00:10:15.750 align:middle line:90%
brought up on a diet of fear.

00:10:15.750 --> 00:10:18.280 align:middle line:84%
I had been brought up
on a diet of fear--

00:10:18.280 --> 00:10:21.180 align:middle line:84%
fear of not being good
enough, fear of failing,

00:10:21.180 --> 00:10:25.020 align:middle line:84%
fear of disappointing
people, fear of illness--

00:10:25.020 --> 00:10:26.820 align:middle line:90%
name it, all the fears--

00:10:26.820 --> 00:10:28.360 align:middle line:90%
fear of failing.

00:10:28.360 --> 00:10:31.710 align:middle line:84%
So my entire life had
been a fear-based life.

00:10:31.710 --> 00:10:33.960 align:middle line:84%
And once all that
fear was gone, it's

00:10:33.960 --> 00:10:37.410 align:middle line:90%
like, wow, this was incredible.

00:10:37.410 --> 00:10:40.780 align:middle line:84%
I just felt so free
and loved and light.

00:10:40.780 --> 00:10:43.770 align:middle line:84%
I realized, for the
first time, that love

00:10:43.770 --> 00:10:47.370 align:middle line:90%
is the absence of fear.

00:10:47.370 --> 00:10:53.400 align:middle line:84%
And I think love exists
all the time, all the time.

00:10:53.400 --> 00:10:58.140 align:middle line:84%
But we don't feel it, because
fear is a denser energy.

00:10:58.140 --> 00:11:04.440 align:middle line:84%
And when I was in the state of
fear, I couldn't feel the love.

00:11:04.440 --> 00:11:09.060 align:middle line:84%
I was in this state of love, and
I realized, for the first time,

00:11:09.060 --> 00:11:12.190 align:middle line:84%
that I had access
to it my whole life.

00:11:12.190 --> 00:11:16.880 align:middle line:84%
We all do, every
single one of us.

00:11:16.880 --> 00:11:22.520 align:middle line:84%
But we haven't accessed it,
because the state of fear

00:11:22.520 --> 00:11:27.635 align:middle line:84%
is so heavy and dense that
the love can't come through.

00:11:27.635 --> 00:11:30.420 align:middle line:90%


00:11:30.420 --> 00:11:37.200 align:middle line:84%
And then-- I apologize for
pausing, but there seems--

00:11:37.200 --> 00:11:39.660 align:middle line:90%
is everything OK?

00:11:39.660 --> 00:11:41.350 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, good.

00:11:41.350 --> 00:11:47.530 align:middle line:90%
>> [INAUDIBLE]

00:11:47.530 --> 00:11:49.993 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, I'll take questions at
the end, if you don't mind.

00:11:49.993 --> 00:11:52.285 align:middle line:84%
I thought you were having
trouble hearing or something,

00:11:52.285 --> 00:11:54.650 align:middle line:90%
that it was something urgent.

00:11:54.650 --> 00:11:55.690 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:11:55.690 --> 00:11:57.680 align:middle line:90%
Sorry about that.

00:11:57.680 --> 00:11:58.480 align:middle line:90%
Sorry.

00:11:58.480 --> 00:12:02.210 align:middle line:90%


00:12:02.210 --> 00:12:12.110 align:middle line:84%
I then became aware that I was
surrounded by beings, entities.

00:12:12.110 --> 00:12:17.610 align:middle line:84%
And I became aware
that I was surrounded

00:12:17.610 --> 00:12:19.740 align:middle line:84%
by entities, and many
of them who I had

00:12:19.740 --> 00:12:23.370 align:middle line:90%
known in this physical life.

00:12:23.370 --> 00:12:25.450 align:middle line:90%
But I didn't know all of them.

00:12:25.450 --> 00:12:27.210 align:middle line:90%
I didn't recognize all of them.

00:12:27.210 --> 00:12:33.750 align:middle line:84%
But all I could feel from them
was pure, unconditional love.

00:12:33.750 --> 00:12:37.140 align:middle line:84%
And I felt like I knew
what they were trying

00:12:37.140 --> 00:12:42.190 align:middle line:84%
to communicate with me,
because we didn't need words

00:12:42.190 --> 00:12:42.990 align:middle line:90%
in that realm.

00:12:42.990 --> 00:12:45.970 align:middle line:90%
There was no language.

00:12:45.970 --> 00:12:48.220 align:middle line:90%
We were just pure essence.

00:12:48.220 --> 00:12:51.780 align:middle line:84%
And I knew what they
wanted me to know.

00:12:51.780 --> 00:12:53.640 align:middle line:84%
And they wanted me
to know that they

00:12:53.640 --> 00:12:56.500 align:middle line:90%
had been with me all the time.

00:12:56.500 --> 00:13:00.300 align:middle line:84%
And one of those essences,
one of those entities,

00:13:00.300 --> 00:13:03.010 align:middle line:90%
was my deceased father--

00:13:03.010 --> 00:13:06.700 align:middle line:84%
my dad, who had passed
away 10 years prior.

00:13:06.700 --> 00:13:09.750 align:middle line:90%


00:13:09.750 --> 00:13:13.950 align:middle line:84%
When I was growing up, I had
a very turbulent relationship

00:13:13.950 --> 00:13:15.690 align:middle line:90%
with my dad.

00:13:15.690 --> 00:13:18.840 align:middle line:84%
And so it was incredible
for me to see him there.

00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:21.380 align:middle line:90%


00:13:21.380 --> 00:13:26.590 align:middle line:90%
See, my parents are Hindus--

00:13:26.590 --> 00:13:27.590 align:middle line:90%
Indian.

00:13:27.590 --> 00:13:30.200 align:middle line:90%
So my ethnicity, I'm Indian.

00:13:30.200 --> 00:13:31.760 align:middle line:90%
But I've never lived in India.

00:13:31.760 --> 00:13:33.890 align:middle line:90%
I grew up in a Western culture.

00:13:33.890 --> 00:13:35.660 align:middle line:90%
I went to a Western school.

00:13:35.660 --> 00:13:40.070 align:middle line:84%
So I had one foot
in each culture.

00:13:40.070 --> 00:13:41.690 align:middle line:90%
My parents were Indian.

00:13:41.690 --> 00:13:45.080 align:middle line:84%
And they were trying to groom
me for an arranged marriage.

00:13:45.080 --> 00:13:47.690 align:middle line:90%
And I rebelled against it.

00:13:47.690 --> 00:13:49.995 align:middle line:84%
And as I was growing
up into my late teens

00:13:49.995 --> 00:13:52.370 align:middle line:84%
and they were trying to groom
me for an arranged marriage

00:13:52.370 --> 00:13:53.750 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't want
to have anything

00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:55.820 align:middle line:84%
to do with an arranged
marriage, because I wanted

00:13:55.820 --> 00:14:00.620 align:middle line:84%
to be independent and go out and
work and study and everything--

00:14:00.620 --> 00:14:06.300 align:middle line:84%
they were trying to get me to
start to prepare to one day

00:14:06.300 --> 00:14:07.100 align:middle line:90%
be married.

00:14:07.100 --> 00:14:08.360 align:middle line:90%
Now, in my culture--

00:14:08.360 --> 00:14:13.820 align:middle line:84%
in Indian culture--
your value as a woman

00:14:13.820 --> 00:14:18.500 align:middle line:84%
is dependent on how valuable
you are to the men in your life.

00:14:18.500 --> 00:14:20.250 align:middle line:90%
That's one thing.

00:14:20.250 --> 00:14:26.030 align:middle line:84%
The second thing is that how
desirable you are as a wife

00:14:26.030 --> 00:14:30.050 align:middle line:84%
is determined by how good
you are at housework.

00:14:30.050 --> 00:14:31.580 align:middle line:90%
And here's the thing--

00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:33.530 align:middle line:90%
I was crap at housework.

00:14:33.530 --> 00:14:36.170 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:36.170 --> 00:14:38.940 align:middle line:90%
I hated housework.

00:14:38.940 --> 00:14:43.810 align:middle line:90%
So I felt totally unvaluable.

00:14:43.810 --> 00:14:47.050 align:middle line:90%
I felt unworthy.

00:14:47.050 --> 00:14:49.510 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
was measured against.

00:14:49.510 --> 00:14:54.850 align:middle line:10%
So also, to give you an idea
of the kind of person I was,

00:14:54.850 --> 00:14:58.900 align:middle line:10%
I was a huge fan
of Cyndi Lauper.

00:14:58.900 --> 00:15:00.520 align:middle line:90%
You remember Cyndi Lauper--

00:15:00.520 --> 00:15:03.910 align:middle line:84%
the "Girls Just Want to
Have Fun" and "True Colors."

00:15:03.910 --> 00:15:05.350 align:middle line:90%
That was me.

00:15:05.350 --> 00:15:07.390 align:middle line:90%
I used to dress like her.

00:15:07.390 --> 00:15:09.070 align:middle line:90%
This was back in the '80s.

00:15:09.070 --> 00:15:13.960 align:middle line:84%
I used to spray my
hair with neon colors.

00:15:13.960 --> 00:15:16.090 align:middle line:84%
And now just imagine,
Hindu parents,

00:15:16.090 --> 00:15:17.920 align:middle line:84%
trying to get their
daughter married.

00:15:17.920 --> 00:15:20.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's like trying
to get Cyndi Lauper

00:15:20.440 --> 00:15:22.180 align:middle line:90%
into an arranged marriage.

00:15:22.180 --> 00:15:24.080 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't going to happen.

00:15:24.080 --> 00:15:25.930 align:middle line:84%
But finally, what
ended up happening--

00:15:25.930 --> 00:15:29.290 align:middle line:84%
see, the other thing
is, Indian women,

00:15:29.290 --> 00:15:31.630 align:middle line:84%
at that time in the
'80s, we were discouraged

00:15:31.630 --> 00:15:35.620 align:middle line:84%
from higher education, as
well, because it made you

00:15:35.620 --> 00:15:38.630 align:middle line:90%
too smart and less desirable.

00:15:38.630 --> 00:15:41.350 align:middle line:84%
And so the less
educated you were,

00:15:41.350 --> 00:15:44.590 align:middle line:84%
the easier it was to get you
married, because otherwise, you

00:15:44.590 --> 00:15:47.920 align:middle line:84%
start to develop a mind of your
own, which they didn't want.

00:15:47.920 --> 00:15:50.530 align:middle line:90%


00:15:50.530 --> 00:15:54.910 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, all my Indian
friends all succumbed.

00:15:54.910 --> 00:15:56.890 align:middle line:90%
And they all got married.

00:15:56.890 --> 00:16:01.490 align:middle line:84%
My Western friends went on to
college, and I became lonely.

00:16:01.490 --> 00:16:05.370 align:middle line:84%
And so I finally succumbed
to an arranged marriage.

00:16:05.370 --> 00:16:08.060 align:middle line:90%
Well, I got engaged to a guy.

00:16:08.060 --> 00:16:09.340 align:middle line:90%
And we were engaged.

00:16:09.340 --> 00:16:11.860 align:middle line:84%
And then when I really started
to see what I got into,

00:16:11.860 --> 00:16:15.120 align:middle line:84%
because I had to learn to
cook his favorite foods

00:16:15.120 --> 00:16:17.370 align:middle line:84%
and learn to clean the house
and learn to do laundry--

00:16:17.370 --> 00:16:19.420 align:middle line:84%
well, all of which
I don't mind doing.

00:16:19.420 --> 00:16:22.930 align:middle line:84%
But I wasn't allowed
to go back to school

00:16:22.930 --> 00:16:25.690 align:middle line:84%
or go to work or
any of these things.

00:16:25.690 --> 00:16:28.390 align:middle line:84%
When I started to understand
what I was getting into,

00:16:28.390 --> 00:16:32.650 align:middle line:84%
three days before the
wedding, I ran away.

00:16:32.650 --> 00:16:34.210 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to
keep in mind, this

00:16:34.210 --> 00:16:36.040 align:middle line:84%
was going to be
an Indian wedding,

00:16:36.040 --> 00:16:37.820 align:middle line:90%
where they book all the venues.

00:16:37.820 --> 00:16:39.760 align:middle line:84%
It's like those
week-long affairs.

00:16:39.760 --> 00:16:42.800 align:middle line:84%
And the relatives fly in
from all over the world.

00:16:42.800 --> 00:16:45.310 align:middle line:84%
So three days before
the wedding, I ran away.

00:16:45.310 --> 00:16:49.250 align:middle line:84%
And I was ostracized
in our community,

00:16:49.250 --> 00:16:55.390 align:middle line:84%
because the way it worked back
then-- this was in 1986, 1987.

00:16:55.390 --> 00:16:58.000 align:middle line:84%
The people in our
community believed

00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:02.630 align:middle line:84%
that if you do that as
a woman, I was spoiled.

00:17:02.630 --> 00:17:05.890 align:middle line:84%
So I was labeled as being
spoiled and choosy and all

00:17:05.890 --> 00:17:08.740 align:middle line:84%
these kinds of things,
which brought a lot of shame

00:17:08.740 --> 00:17:10.990 align:middle line:90%
to my family and my parents.

00:17:10.990 --> 00:17:14.170 align:middle line:84%
My parents were told that no
other Indian man would marry me

00:17:14.170 --> 00:17:16.450 align:middle line:90%
after what I had done.

00:17:16.450 --> 00:17:18.940 align:middle line:84%
So they had to deal
with all of that.

00:17:18.940 --> 00:17:22.839 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, I really thought I
had brought a lot of shame

00:17:22.839 --> 00:17:25.450 align:middle line:90%
to my family and to my dad.

00:17:25.450 --> 00:17:32.250 align:middle line:84%
And when I did finally marry
the man that I did marry,

00:17:32.250 --> 00:17:35.500 align:middle line:90%
my dad had already passed away.

00:17:35.500 --> 00:17:40.470 align:middle line:84%
And so here he was now
on the other side--

00:17:40.470 --> 00:17:45.300 align:middle line:84%
my dad and me, his
essence and my essence.

00:17:45.300 --> 00:17:50.710 align:middle line:84%
And I thought that I would
get judgment from him.

00:17:50.710 --> 00:17:53.860 align:middle line:84%
I had carried the guilt of
letting him down and letting

00:17:53.860 --> 00:17:55.600 align:middle line:90%
my family down.

00:17:55.600 --> 00:18:01.000 align:middle line:84%
But all I felt from him was
pure, unconditional love,

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:03.610 align:middle line:90%
empathy, and compassion.

00:18:03.610 --> 00:18:08.470 align:middle line:84%
And what I realized is
that when we cross over

00:18:08.470 --> 00:18:12.910 align:middle line:84%
from here, when we
die, we don't just

00:18:12.910 --> 00:18:17.200 align:middle line:90%
leave behind our physical body.

00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:23.900 align:middle line:84%
We leave behind our gender,
our culture, our race,

00:18:23.900 --> 00:18:29.260 align:middle line:84%
our religion, and all
the layers of beliefs

00:18:29.260 --> 00:18:32.950 align:middle line:84%
and filters and
lenses that we've

00:18:32.950 --> 00:18:36.140 align:middle line:90%
accumulated over a lifetime.

00:18:36.140 --> 00:18:39.680 align:middle line:90%
We leave all of that behind.

00:18:39.680 --> 00:18:46.070 align:middle line:84%
So if we leave all of that
behind, what crosses over?

00:18:46.070 --> 00:18:52.230 align:middle line:84%
What crosses over is
our pure essence--

00:18:52.230 --> 00:18:55.220 align:middle line:84%
our pure essence, which,
to me, is the same

00:18:55.220 --> 00:19:00.150 align:middle line:90%
as pure love or pure God.

00:19:00.150 --> 00:19:01.795 align:middle line:90%
We can call it whatever we want.

00:19:01.795 --> 00:19:04.410 align:middle line:90%


00:19:04.410 --> 00:19:07.710 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that
just as much as I

00:19:07.710 --> 00:19:11.710 align:middle line:84%
had been a victim of my
culture while I was growing up,

00:19:11.710 --> 00:19:13.680 align:middle line:84%
my dad was a victim
of the same culture.

00:19:13.680 --> 00:19:16.190 align:middle line:90%


00:19:16.190 --> 00:19:19.190 align:middle line:84%
At the end of it, we're
all victims of our filters

00:19:19.190 --> 00:19:22.940 align:middle line:84%
and our upbringing and
our genders and so on,

00:19:22.940 --> 00:19:25.510 align:middle line:90%
our cultures.

00:19:25.510 --> 00:19:31.360 align:middle line:84%
And here we were, both of
us, without any of that, just

00:19:31.360 --> 00:19:32.870 align:middle line:90%
our pure essence--

00:19:32.870 --> 00:19:36.040 align:middle line:84%
my dad's pure essence
and my pure essence.

00:19:36.040 --> 00:19:41.950 align:middle line:84%
And all we had for each other
was pure, unconditional love.

00:19:41.950 --> 00:19:44.200 align:middle line:84%
And unconditional
love is something

00:19:44.200 --> 00:19:47.500 align:middle line:84%
that goes beyond
forgiveness, because in order

00:19:47.500 --> 00:19:50.530 align:middle line:84%
to forgive someone, you
have to believe that they

00:19:50.530 --> 00:19:52.310 align:middle line:90%
have done something wrong.

00:19:52.310 --> 00:19:54.280 align:middle line:90%
So you have to judge them first.

00:19:54.280 --> 00:19:56.680 align:middle line:84%
And then it's like, I'm
going to forgive you

00:19:56.680 --> 00:19:58.600 align:middle line:90%
for what you've done wrong.

00:19:58.600 --> 00:20:00.520 align:middle line:90%
In that state, it's beyond that.

00:20:00.520 --> 00:20:02.680 align:middle line:84%
You see right
through the person,

00:20:02.680 --> 00:20:05.890 align:middle line:84%
and you understand why
they did what they did.

00:20:05.890 --> 00:20:09.650 align:middle line:84%
So all you have for them
is compassion and empathy.

00:20:09.650 --> 00:20:13.080 align:middle line:84%
So forgiveness is
not even needed.

00:20:13.080 --> 00:20:16.500 align:middle line:84%
It goes right to the
soul, the heart, the love,

00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:19.290 align:middle line:90%
the essence of the person.

00:20:19.290 --> 00:20:23.120 align:middle line:84%
That's what it felt
like on the other side.

00:20:23.120 --> 00:20:29.990 align:middle line:84%
I realized that every single one
of us have access to that state

00:20:29.990 --> 00:20:32.900 align:middle line:90%
all the time.

00:20:32.900 --> 00:20:39.130 align:middle line:84%
But all the filters just
crowd it out, block it out.

00:20:39.130 --> 00:20:42.160 align:middle line:84%
Everything was so crystal
clear there-- everything.

00:20:42.160 --> 00:20:44.440 align:middle line:90%
Everything was sharper.

00:20:44.440 --> 00:20:47.170 align:middle line:90%
The colors were sharper.

00:20:47.170 --> 00:20:51.430 align:middle line:84%
And wherever I put my
awareness, I could be there.

00:20:51.430 --> 00:20:54.880 align:middle line:84%
My awareness then
went to my brother.

00:20:54.880 --> 00:20:59.110 align:middle line:84%
And I actually knew,
without having been told,

00:20:59.110 --> 00:21:05.860 align:middle line:84%
that he was on his way to fly
down to see me before I died.

00:21:05.860 --> 00:21:10.030 align:middle line:84%
And I started to know that,
oh, my physical body better

00:21:10.030 --> 00:21:12.790 align:middle line:84%
stay alive a little bit
longer, or my brother will

00:21:12.790 --> 00:21:17.330 align:middle line:84%
be distraught if he gets
there and I'll be dead.

00:21:17.330 --> 00:21:19.640 align:middle line:84%
Literally, I could
see whatever--

00:21:19.640 --> 00:21:23.780 align:middle line:84%
wherever I put my awareness,
that's what I could see.

00:21:23.780 --> 00:21:25.280 align:middle line:90%
I was aware of other lives.

00:21:25.280 --> 00:21:29.240 align:middle line:84%
But they felt like they were
happening right here and now.

00:21:29.240 --> 00:21:32.330 align:middle line:84%
I was aware of a
life that I interpret

00:21:32.330 --> 00:21:35.090 align:middle line:84%
as a past life,
where I recognized

00:21:35.090 --> 00:21:36.650 align:middle line:90%
my brother, my husband.

00:21:36.650 --> 00:21:39.410 align:middle line:90%
But they had other roles.

00:21:39.410 --> 00:21:43.770 align:middle line:84%
I could see my future pan
out before me, as well.

00:21:43.770 --> 00:21:48.320 align:middle line:84%
But I had the choice of
whether to come back or not.

00:21:48.320 --> 00:21:51.080 align:middle line:90%


00:21:51.080 --> 00:21:52.580 align:middle line:84%
I had the choice
of whether I wanted

00:21:52.580 --> 00:21:55.100 align:middle line:84%
to come back into
this physical body

00:21:55.100 --> 00:21:59.170 align:middle line:84%
and live out the rest
of this life or not.

00:21:59.170 --> 00:22:03.400 align:middle line:84%
And it was so beautiful on
that side that no part of me

00:22:03.400 --> 00:22:09.520 align:middle line:84%
wanted to come back,
because my body was sick.

00:22:09.520 --> 00:22:13.870 align:middle line:84%
And it was in so
much pain that I

00:22:13.870 --> 00:22:15.520 align:middle line:84%
didn't see any
reason to come back,

00:22:15.520 --> 00:22:17.530 align:middle line:90%
because I had been suffering.

00:22:17.530 --> 00:22:19.120 align:middle line:90%
My family had been suffering.

00:22:19.120 --> 00:22:21.790 align:middle line:84%
There was no reason
to come back.

00:22:21.790 --> 00:22:26.590 align:middle line:84%
But in those moments, because
I was in this state of clarity,

00:22:26.590 --> 00:22:30.790 align:middle line:84%
it's like, as soon as I would
have a thought, an awareness,

00:22:30.790 --> 00:22:34.550 align:middle line:84%
a focus on something, the
answer would come right away.

00:22:34.550 --> 00:22:37.000 align:middle line:84%
It was like, immediately,
the answer would come.

00:22:37.000 --> 00:22:40.270 align:middle line:84%
In that state of clarity,
I was understanding

00:22:40.270 --> 00:22:42.850 align:middle line:90%
why I had the cancer.

00:22:42.850 --> 00:22:47.620 align:middle line:84%
I understood how every thought
and every decision that

00:22:47.620 --> 00:22:50.650 align:middle line:84%
had been made from
a place of fear

00:22:50.650 --> 00:22:55.990 align:middle line:84%
had contributed to me
lying on that hospital

00:22:55.990 --> 00:22:58.660 align:middle line:90%
bed in that moment, dying.

00:22:58.660 --> 00:23:01.690 align:middle line:84%
I understood how and why
it was that I was dying.

00:23:01.690 --> 00:23:04.210 align:middle line:84%
I understood what
my purpose had been.

00:23:04.210 --> 00:23:09.010 align:middle line:84%
I understood what my intention
had been when I first

00:23:09.010 --> 00:23:10.840 align:middle line:90%
came into this world.

00:23:10.840 --> 00:23:15.010 align:middle line:84%
I understood how
I had lost my way.

00:23:15.010 --> 00:23:17.170 align:middle line:90%
All of that was so clear to me.

00:23:17.170 --> 00:23:19.700 align:middle line:90%


00:23:19.700 --> 00:23:23.600 align:middle line:84%
And then I started
to get the clarity

00:23:23.600 --> 00:23:26.860 align:middle line:90%
that if I chose to go back--

00:23:26.860 --> 00:23:30.200 align:middle line:84%
and I feel it was my dad
that was helping me to get

00:23:30.200 --> 00:23:32.360 align:middle line:90%
to this place of clarity--

00:23:32.360 --> 00:23:37.130 align:middle line:84%
that if I chose to go back,
now that I knew this--

00:23:37.130 --> 00:23:39.320 align:middle line:90%
now that I knew this truth--

00:23:39.320 --> 00:23:42.200 align:middle line:84%
that my body would heal
very, very quickly.

00:23:42.200 --> 00:23:48.670 align:middle line:84%
I started to understand that
illness is not physical.

00:23:48.670 --> 00:23:51.060 align:middle line:90%
It's metaphysical.

00:23:51.060 --> 00:23:54.480 align:middle line:84%
And I understood that my
physical body was only

00:23:54.480 --> 00:23:57.660 align:middle line:84%
a reflection of the
metaphysical me--

00:23:57.660 --> 00:24:01.260 align:middle line:90%
the soul me, the rest of me.

00:24:01.260 --> 00:24:02.930 align:middle line:84%
And I started to
understand, because I

00:24:02.930 --> 00:24:04.940 align:middle line:90%
had feared all the treatments.

00:24:04.940 --> 00:24:05.900 align:middle line:90%
I feared cancer.

00:24:05.900 --> 00:24:07.610 align:middle line:90%
I feared the treatments.

00:24:07.610 --> 00:24:11.330 align:middle line:84%
And I started to understand,
while I was there,

00:24:11.330 --> 00:24:15.750 align:middle line:84%
that what I had, what
I was going through,

00:24:15.750 --> 00:24:19.080 align:middle line:84%
my physical illness,
was not something

00:24:19.080 --> 00:24:21.540 align:middle line:84%
that was treatable
from the physical,

00:24:21.540 --> 00:24:24.690 align:middle line:84%
because it was my choice
whether I wanted to stay or go.

00:24:24.690 --> 00:24:26.970 align:middle line:84%
The interesting thing,
also, was that I

00:24:26.970 --> 00:24:32.760 align:middle line:84%
was shown what I would be
doing if I chose to come back.

00:24:32.760 --> 00:24:37.240 align:middle line:84%
I was shown that the illness
would heal very, very quickly.

00:24:37.240 --> 00:24:39.360 align:middle line:84%
But I wasn't forced
to come back.

00:24:39.360 --> 00:24:44.280 align:middle line:84%
I was even shown that
if I chose to leave,

00:24:44.280 --> 00:24:46.290 align:middle line:84%
my medical records
would show that I

00:24:46.290 --> 00:24:51.710 align:middle line:84%
died from organ failure
due to end-stage cancer.

00:24:51.710 --> 00:24:55.070 align:middle line:84%
But if I chose to
go back, my organs

00:24:55.070 --> 00:24:57.960 align:middle line:90%
would start functioning again.

00:24:57.960 --> 00:25:00.090 align:middle line:90%
And so I could see all of this.

00:25:00.090 --> 00:25:01.800 align:middle line:90%
And it was so clear.

00:25:01.800 --> 00:25:04.680 align:middle line:84%
And that's when my dad
started to say to me,

00:25:04.680 --> 00:25:07.720 align:middle line:90%
it's not your time.

00:25:07.720 --> 00:25:12.450 align:middle line:84%
If you don't go back, you won't
have fulfilled your purpose.

00:25:12.450 --> 00:25:15.960 align:middle line:84%
And he told me that my husband's
purpose was linked to mine.

00:25:15.960 --> 00:25:18.630 align:middle line:84%
Now, I had felt so sad that
my dad hadn't been there

00:25:18.630 --> 00:25:21.240 align:middle line:84%
to see my husband
and I get married.

00:25:21.240 --> 00:25:24.150 align:middle line:84%
He wanted me to know
that he was there.

00:25:24.150 --> 00:25:28.850 align:middle line:84%
He had seen us get married,
even though I couldn't see him.

00:25:28.850 --> 00:25:34.280 align:middle line:84%
And he wanted me to know that
I was meant to be with Danny.

00:25:34.280 --> 00:25:37.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's why it didn't work
with the previous person.

00:25:37.790 --> 00:25:41.000 align:middle line:84%
Danny was my soul
mate, is my soul mate,

00:25:41.000 --> 00:25:42.300 align:middle line:90%
and that we had a purpose.

00:25:42.300 --> 00:25:44.450 align:middle line:90%
And our purpose was linked.

00:25:44.450 --> 00:25:46.310 align:middle line:84%
And if I didn't go
back, he wouldn't

00:25:46.310 --> 00:25:48.305 align:middle line:84%
be able to fulfill
his purpose, either.

00:25:48.305 --> 00:25:51.090 align:middle line:90%


00:25:51.090 --> 00:25:54.230 align:middle line:84%
And so it was in
that moment that I

00:25:54.230 --> 00:25:57.040 align:middle line:90%
made the choice to go back.

00:25:57.040 --> 00:26:04.280 align:middle line:84%
And in that moment, my dad said,
now that you know this truth,

00:26:04.280 --> 00:26:09.300 align:middle line:84%
go back and live
your life fearlessly.

00:26:09.300 --> 00:26:11.280 align:middle line:84%
And it was in those
moments that I started

00:26:11.280 --> 00:26:13.570 align:middle line:90%
to come out of the coma.

00:26:13.570 --> 00:26:17.120 align:middle line:84%
And when I came out of the
coma, I saw my family around me.

00:26:17.120 --> 00:26:18.410 align:middle line:90%
My brother was there.

00:26:18.410 --> 00:26:19.860 align:middle line:90%
He'd gotten off the plane.

00:26:19.860 --> 00:26:26.110 align:middle line:84%
And he was right there, and
my mom, and my husband, Danny.

00:26:26.110 --> 00:26:27.870 align:middle line:84%
And I started to
come out of the coma.

00:26:27.870 --> 00:26:30.430 align:middle line:84%
I'd been in the coma for
only a day and a half--

00:26:30.430 --> 00:26:31.870 align:middle line:90%
about 30 hours.

00:26:31.870 --> 00:26:35.140 align:middle line:84%
So I'd gone in the coma
on February the 2nd.

00:26:35.140 --> 00:26:39.200 align:middle line:84%
I came out of it on
February the 3rd.

00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:42.620 align:middle line:84%
And I was still really groggy,
like one foot on each side.

00:26:42.620 --> 00:26:45.510 align:middle line:84%
And I was saying to them,
I'm going to be fine.

00:26:45.510 --> 00:26:47.090 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
worry about me.

00:26:47.090 --> 00:26:49.460 align:middle line:84%
Dad told me it's
not my time to go.

00:26:49.460 --> 00:26:50.555 align:middle line:90%
He's here.

00:26:50.555 --> 00:26:55.490 align:middle line:84%
So they didn't know what
I was talking about.

00:26:55.490 --> 00:26:56.430 align:middle line:90%
So they said, what?

00:26:56.430 --> 00:26:57.780 align:middle line:90%
What are you talking about?

00:26:57.780 --> 00:27:00.380 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I'm fine, really.

00:27:00.380 --> 00:27:02.810 align:middle line:84%
And then I started
to tell them things

00:27:02.810 --> 00:27:06.860 align:middle line:84%
that had been happening in the
room while I was in the coma--

00:27:06.860 --> 00:27:10.730 align:middle line:84%
things which there was
no way for me to know.

00:27:10.730 --> 00:27:13.620 align:middle line:84%
And so they knew something
strange had happened.

00:27:13.620 --> 00:27:15.410 align:middle line:84%
They called my
doctor to come in.

00:27:15.410 --> 00:27:18.800 align:middle line:84%
And when the doctor came in,
I started to tell him things

00:27:18.800 --> 00:27:21.500 align:middle line:84%
like, oh, you took
fluid out of my lungs.

00:27:21.500 --> 00:27:23.210 align:middle line:84%
I was choking at
4:00 in the morning,

00:27:23.210 --> 00:27:25.130 align:middle line:84%
and you took fluid
out of my lungs.

00:27:25.130 --> 00:27:27.140 align:middle line:90%
And he said, how do you know?

00:27:27.140 --> 00:27:28.010 align:middle line:90%
You were in a coma.

00:27:28.010 --> 00:27:30.170 align:middle line:84%
There's no way you
could know that.

00:27:30.170 --> 00:27:34.910 align:middle line:84%
And then I said
to Danny, I said,

00:27:34.910 --> 00:27:39.710 align:middle line:84%
that's the doctor that told you
that these are my final hours,

00:27:39.710 --> 00:27:41.970 align:middle line:84%
that I'm not even going to
make it through the night.

00:27:41.970 --> 00:27:45.650 align:middle line:84%
And Danny said, there's no
way you could have heard that.

00:27:45.650 --> 00:27:48.920 align:middle line:84%
He said that to me down the
hallway, about 40 feet away

00:27:48.920 --> 00:27:50.330 align:middle line:90%
from your room.

00:27:50.330 --> 00:27:53.300 align:middle line:84%
And so all these things
started to come up,

00:27:53.300 --> 00:27:54.830 align:middle line:90%
where I was describing things.

00:27:54.830 --> 00:27:59.880 align:middle line:84%
I was describing the nurse who
was poking tubes into my veins.

00:27:59.880 --> 00:28:01.250 align:middle line:90%
And it was a male nurse.

00:28:01.250 --> 00:28:02.750 align:middle line:90%
And he couldn't find my veins.

00:28:02.750 --> 00:28:05.570 align:middle line:84%
And he was actually saying,
her veins have retracted.

00:28:05.570 --> 00:28:08.480 align:middle line:84%
And they were resigning
themselves to the fact

00:28:08.480 --> 00:28:10.340 align:middle line:90%
that it was too late, anyway.

00:28:10.340 --> 00:28:12.080 align:middle line:90%
I was gone, anyway.

00:28:12.080 --> 00:28:15.960 align:middle line:84%
And so I was recollecting
all of this for all of them.

00:28:15.960 --> 00:28:18.080 align:middle line:90%
And they were really surprised.

00:28:18.080 --> 00:28:26.090 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, within four days,
the tumors shrunk by 70%.

00:28:26.090 --> 00:28:28.010 align:middle line:84%
The doctors didn't
even know what

00:28:28.010 --> 00:28:31.010 align:middle line:90%
to write in my medical records.

00:28:31.010 --> 00:28:35.540 align:middle line:84%
My oncologist made the
gesture of throwing

00:28:35.540 --> 00:28:37.880 align:middle line:90%
my file into the trash.

00:28:37.880 --> 00:28:40.440 align:middle line:84%
He was like, I don't even
know what to write in here.

00:28:40.440 --> 00:28:42.830 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know
what to make of you.

00:28:42.830 --> 00:28:44.000 align:middle line:90%
That's what he said.

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:46.700 align:middle line:84%
I am so grateful this happened
to me in the hospital,

00:28:46.700 --> 00:28:50.150 align:middle line:84%
because I have the medical
records to prove it,

00:28:50.150 --> 00:28:53.060 align:middle line:84%
because I wasn't aware
of the challenges

00:28:53.060 --> 00:28:54.710 align:middle line:84%
that I would get
later from people

00:28:54.710 --> 00:28:56.870 align:middle line:90%
who question and question.

00:28:56.870 --> 00:29:01.100 align:middle line:84%
So I'm so thankful that
it happened in a hospital.

00:29:01.100 --> 00:29:05.810 align:middle line:84%
But as I said, four days later,
after coming out of the coma,

00:29:05.810 --> 00:29:08.270 align:middle line:90%
the tumors shrunk by 70%.

00:29:08.270 --> 00:29:12.170 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to pull
all the tubes and--

00:29:12.170 --> 00:29:15.620 align:middle line:90%
I was off the breathing tube.

00:29:15.620 --> 00:29:18.248 align:middle line:90%
I was off the nutrition tube.

00:29:18.248 --> 00:29:22.700 align:middle line:84%
And I was off on a lot
of these different tubes.

00:29:22.700 --> 00:29:25.160 align:middle line:84%
And I was sitting up,
and I was talking.

00:29:25.160 --> 00:29:27.410 align:middle line:84%
And the doctors really just
couldn't figure it out.

00:29:27.410 --> 00:29:30.840 align:middle line:84%
Oh, and my organs started
functioning again.

00:29:30.840 --> 00:29:32.630 align:middle line:84%
And I had these
open skin lesions,

00:29:32.630 --> 00:29:35.450 align:middle line:84%
which the doctors
thought that they

00:29:35.450 --> 00:29:40.100 align:middle line:84%
would need to use reconstructive
surgery to heal them,

00:29:40.100 --> 00:29:43.850 align:middle line:84%
because they said, your body
is so weak and so devoid

00:29:43.850 --> 00:29:49.430 align:middle line:84%
of nutrition, you don't have
the strength for that to heal.

00:29:49.430 --> 00:29:51.920 align:middle line:90%
They healed by themselves.

00:29:51.920 --> 00:29:56.120 align:middle line:84%
In three and 1/2 weeks, they
could find no trace of cancer

00:29:56.120 --> 00:29:57.283 align:middle line:90%
in my body.

00:29:57.283 --> 00:29:59.200 align:middle line:84%
They were just waiting
for me to get stronger.

00:29:59.200 --> 00:30:06.050 align:middle line:84%
Two weeks later, I was strong
enough to leave the hospital

00:30:06.050 --> 00:30:10.100 align:middle line:84%
and go home and to live
my life cancer-free.

00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:13.530 align:middle line:90%
And that was 13 years ago.

00:30:13.530 --> 00:30:14.330 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:30:14.330 --> 00:30:14.805 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:30:14.805 --> 00:30:15.755 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:30:15.755 --> 00:30:20.990 align:middle line:90%


00:30:20.990 --> 00:30:21.980 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:30:21.980 --> 00:30:27.380 align:middle line:84%
So now, though, you'd
think that, OK, I go home,

00:30:27.380 --> 00:30:31.580 align:middle line:84%
live my life cancer-free, and
it's all peachy and roses.

00:30:31.580 --> 00:30:34.130 align:middle line:84%
But let me tell
you something, that

00:30:34.130 --> 00:30:38.090 align:middle line:84%
was when the challenge began,
because here's what happens.

00:30:38.090 --> 00:30:44.000 align:middle line:84%
When I went home, I realized
the person that came out

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:47.480 align:middle line:84%
of the hospital was a different
person from the one who

00:30:47.480 --> 00:30:50.470 align:middle line:90%
went into the hospital.

00:30:50.470 --> 00:30:52.960 align:middle line:84%
The person that went
into the hospital

00:30:52.960 --> 00:30:56.140 align:middle line:84%
was someone who was
really scared of cancer,

00:30:56.140 --> 00:31:00.190 align:middle line:84%
really scared of disappointing
people, really scared

00:31:00.190 --> 00:31:01.580 align:middle line:90%
of letting people down.

00:31:01.580 --> 00:31:03.190 align:middle line:90%
I was really scared of illness.

00:31:03.190 --> 00:31:07.120 align:middle line:84%
Every decision I made in
my life came from a place

00:31:07.120 --> 00:31:11.030 align:middle line:90%
of fear instead of love.

00:31:11.030 --> 00:31:13.470 align:middle line:90%
I was a people-pleaser.

00:31:13.470 --> 00:31:15.690 align:middle line:90%
I was a doormat.

00:31:15.690 --> 00:31:19.000 align:middle line:90%
I had completely lost myself.

00:31:19.000 --> 00:31:24.070 align:middle line:84%
Now I realize that the most
important thing I could do

00:31:24.070 --> 00:31:28.720 align:middle line:84%
was to love and honor
myself and to be who I am--

00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:30.580 align:middle line:90%
to truly be who I am.

00:31:30.580 --> 00:31:33.650 align:middle line:90%


00:31:33.650 --> 00:31:39.680 align:middle line:84%
And I was, in a strange
way, a little bit

00:31:39.680 --> 00:31:42.860 align:middle line:84%
scared of doing it
in the community

00:31:42.860 --> 00:31:47.270 align:middle line:84%
that I was in, because
the community was

00:31:47.270 --> 00:31:52.440 align:middle line:84%
the community I was in that I
had built as a people-pleaser.

00:31:52.440 --> 00:31:58.740 align:middle line:84%
And I knew that if I was to go
back to the life I had before

00:31:58.740 --> 00:32:01.770 align:middle line:84%
and be the person
I was before, that

00:32:01.770 --> 00:32:07.910 align:middle line:84%
was the person who got cancer,
because I now knew that cancer

00:32:07.910 --> 00:32:10.040 align:middle line:90%
is not a physical disease.

00:32:10.040 --> 00:32:14.780 align:middle line:84%
I understood that the
cancer was not my enemy.

00:32:14.780 --> 00:32:17.100 align:middle line:84%
People say to me, the
cancer damn near killed you.

00:32:17.100 --> 00:32:21.500 align:middle line:10%
And I say, no, I was killing
myself before the cancer.

00:32:21.500 --> 00:32:26.240 align:middle line:84%
The cancer came to
me to save my life.

00:32:26.240 --> 00:32:29.590 align:middle line:90%
And I wasn't listening to it.

00:32:29.590 --> 00:32:34.990 align:middle line:84%
And so I continued
to not listen to it.

00:32:34.990 --> 00:32:38.970 align:middle line:84%
I continued to not listen
to the wake-up calls

00:32:38.970 --> 00:32:40.950 align:middle line:90%
until I reached near-death.

00:32:40.950 --> 00:32:43.680 align:middle line:84%
I tell people, I couldn't
have been very smart

00:32:43.680 --> 00:32:46.590 align:middle line:84%
that it took death for
me to realize this--

00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:51.330 align:middle line:84%
that it took death for me to
realize that all I have to do

00:32:51.330 --> 00:32:53.580 align:middle line:90%
is be myself.

00:32:53.580 --> 00:32:55.290 align:middle line:90%
And that is the crux of it.

00:32:55.290 --> 00:32:58.740 align:middle line:84%
When I learned that
I had to come back

00:32:58.740 --> 00:33:01.350 align:middle line:90%
and fulfill my purpose--

00:33:01.350 --> 00:33:04.270 align:middle line:84%
your purpose, your purpose,
your purpose, your purpose,

00:33:04.270 --> 00:33:07.180 align:middle line:90%
and my purpose are all the same.

00:33:07.180 --> 00:33:10.830 align:middle line:84%
It's actually very simple, but
we make it really complicated.

00:33:10.830 --> 00:33:14.670 align:middle line:90%
Our purpose is to be who we are.

00:33:14.670 --> 00:33:16.050 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:33:16.050 --> 00:33:18.490 align:middle line:90%
It's nothing more than that.

00:33:18.490 --> 00:33:22.260 align:middle line:90%
And it's also to love ourselves.

00:33:22.260 --> 00:33:24.540 align:middle line:84%
And what do I mean
by "love ourselves"?

00:33:24.540 --> 00:33:27.450 align:middle line:84%
Many people think
that loving ourselves

00:33:27.450 --> 00:33:34.720 align:middle line:84%
means just going for massages
and going for spa dates

00:33:34.720 --> 00:33:35.630 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:33:35.630 --> 00:33:38.720 align:middle line:84%
And people say, I love
myself, I treat myself a lot,

00:33:38.720 --> 00:33:42.070 align:middle line:84%
but my life still
isn't working for me.

00:33:42.070 --> 00:33:45.190 align:middle line:84%
And how many of you think
loving yourself is selfish?

00:33:45.190 --> 00:33:47.050 align:middle line:84%
Or how many of you
were brought up

00:33:47.050 --> 00:33:49.840 align:middle line:84%
to believe that loving
yourself is selfish?

00:33:49.840 --> 00:33:50.860 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:33:50.860 --> 00:33:53.440 align:middle line:84%
So I was brought up to
believe that loving myself

00:33:53.440 --> 00:33:54.300 align:middle line:90%
is selfish, too.

00:33:54.300 --> 00:33:55.300 align:middle line:90%
And quite a lot of you--

00:33:55.300 --> 00:33:58.450 align:middle line:90%
I saw a lot of hands go up.

00:33:58.450 --> 00:34:01.930 align:middle line:84%
Here's where I learned
completely differently

00:34:01.930 --> 00:34:04.760 align:middle line:90%
on the other side.

00:34:04.760 --> 00:34:07.880 align:middle line:84%
What I realized is
that we are all much

00:34:07.880 --> 00:34:10.280 align:middle line:90%
more than our physical bodies.

00:34:10.280 --> 00:34:14.260 align:middle line:10%
So I want you to imagine this.

00:34:14.260 --> 00:34:16.800 align:middle line:90%
Imagine an iceberg.

00:34:16.800 --> 00:34:20.159 align:middle line:84%
When you look at an
iceberg, even a picture

00:34:20.159 --> 00:34:22.980 align:middle line:84%
of an iceberg, what
you're really seeing

00:34:22.980 --> 00:34:25.179 align:middle line:90%
is just the tip of the iceberg.

00:34:25.179 --> 00:34:26.220 align:middle line:90%
Does everyone know that?

00:34:26.220 --> 00:34:28.530 align:middle line:90%
That most of the iceberg--

00:34:28.530 --> 00:34:30.900 align:middle line:84%
a much bigger part
of the iceberg--

00:34:30.900 --> 00:34:32.760 align:middle line:90%
is beneath the water.

00:34:32.760 --> 00:34:34.820 align:middle line:90%
And you can't see it.

00:34:34.820 --> 00:34:37.739 align:middle line:84%
There's about 80%
more iceberg that you

00:34:37.739 --> 00:34:40.770 align:middle line:90%
can't see than you can.

00:34:40.770 --> 00:34:42.090 align:middle line:90%
It's the same with us.

00:34:42.090 --> 00:34:45.440 align:middle line:90%
It's the same with you and me.

00:34:45.440 --> 00:34:50.400 align:middle line:90%
80% of us, you can't see.

00:34:50.400 --> 00:34:55.060 align:middle line:84%
And we never developed a
language to tap into it.

00:34:55.060 --> 00:34:58.360 align:middle line:84%
When we were born, we knew
that we were much more

00:34:58.360 --> 00:35:00.310 align:middle line:90%
than our physical bodies.

00:35:00.310 --> 00:35:02.650 align:middle line:84%
What you see here--
your physical body,

00:35:02.650 --> 00:35:04.090 align:middle line:90%
my physical body--

00:35:04.090 --> 00:35:07.870 align:middle line:84%
is only a small percentage
of who we really are.

00:35:07.870 --> 00:35:10.660 align:middle line:84%
When I died, I realized
I was much bigger.

00:35:10.660 --> 00:35:13.480 align:middle line:84%
My space takes up
much more space

00:35:13.480 --> 00:35:15.760 align:middle line:90%
than just where I'm standing.

00:35:15.760 --> 00:35:20.270 align:middle line:84%
And so does yours and yours and
yours and yours and all of you.

00:35:20.270 --> 00:35:21.970 align:middle line:84%
And we can actually
sense each other,

00:35:21.970 --> 00:35:24.820 align:middle line:84%
whether we care to
admit it or not.

00:35:24.820 --> 00:35:26.680 align:middle line:84%
Why do you think
your pet dog knows

00:35:26.680 --> 00:35:31.280 align:middle line:84%
when you're coming home long
before your dog can see you?

00:35:31.280 --> 00:35:34.580 align:middle line:84%
Because they're aware of
the rest of their iceberg.

00:35:34.580 --> 00:35:37.280 align:middle line:90%
We have denied it from birth.

00:35:37.280 --> 00:35:40.230 align:middle line:84%
We've not even
given it language.

00:35:40.230 --> 00:35:43.520 align:middle line:84%
So we don't even
consider it a thing.

00:35:43.520 --> 00:35:45.890 align:middle line:84%
And when you are aware
of it as a child,

00:35:45.890 --> 00:35:48.360 align:middle line:84%
you're told it's
your imagination.

00:35:48.360 --> 00:35:52.250 align:middle line:84%
And so you start to push it out
and push it away and deny it.

00:35:52.250 --> 00:35:54.800 align:middle line:84%
And we have been
told that all we are

00:35:54.800 --> 00:35:59.180 align:middle line:84%
is five sensory,
three-dimensional physical

00:35:59.180 --> 00:36:00.630 align:middle line:90%
beings.

00:36:00.630 --> 00:36:03.086 align:middle line:90%
But in actuality, we're not.

00:36:03.086 --> 00:36:04.580 align:middle line:90%
We're not.

00:36:04.580 --> 00:36:09.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's why we're living
in so much fear, because we

00:36:09.530 --> 00:36:12.180 align:middle line:90%
don't see the whole picture.

00:36:12.180 --> 00:36:14.900 align:middle line:90%
We don't see the whole iceberg.

00:36:14.900 --> 00:36:18.280 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I discovered
when I was in the other side--

00:36:18.280 --> 00:36:21.440 align:middle line:90%
that we are all connected.

00:36:21.440 --> 00:36:22.730 align:middle line:90%
We're all connected.

00:36:22.730 --> 00:36:25.070 align:middle line:90%
We're all in this hole together.

00:36:25.070 --> 00:36:28.310 align:middle line:84%
And there is so much more to
us than this physical body.

00:36:28.310 --> 00:36:32.960 align:middle line:84%
And that "more" part of us
overlaps with everybody.

00:36:32.960 --> 00:36:35.670 align:middle line:84%
So if I am in fear,
what am I doing?

00:36:35.670 --> 00:36:38.450 align:middle line:84%
I'm taking this fear
with me wherever I go.

00:36:38.450 --> 00:36:42.810 align:middle line:84%
If I don't love myself and I
loathe myself, what am I doing?

00:36:42.810 --> 00:36:44.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm taking it with
me wherever I go.

00:36:44.730 --> 00:36:47.390 align:middle line:84%
And I'm spreading it
to everybody around me,

00:36:47.390 --> 00:36:50.270 align:middle line:84%
because the rest of my
iceberg is touching yours

00:36:50.270 --> 00:36:51.920 align:middle line:90%
and yours and yours.

00:36:51.920 --> 00:36:53.810 align:middle line:84%
And this is what
we're doing today.

00:36:53.810 --> 00:36:56.060 align:middle line:84%
Why do you think there's
so much fear in the world?

00:36:56.060 --> 00:36:57.560 align:middle line:90%
Because we don't realize it.

00:36:57.560 --> 00:36:58.550 align:middle line:90%
We're sharing fear.

00:36:58.550 --> 00:37:01.280 align:middle line:90%
We're spreading fear.

00:37:01.280 --> 00:37:03.010 align:middle line:90%
What is love?

00:37:03.010 --> 00:37:05.320 align:middle line:90%
Love is the absence of fear.

00:37:05.320 --> 00:37:10.120 align:middle line:84%
To me, love is realizing
you are the whole iceberg.

00:37:10.120 --> 00:37:13.960 align:middle line:84%
Fear is thinking you're just
the tip of the iceberg--

00:37:13.960 --> 00:37:16.120 align:middle line:90%
that this is all I am.

00:37:16.120 --> 00:37:19.360 align:middle line:84%
And my tip of the
iceberg has to please

00:37:19.360 --> 00:37:23.380 align:middle line:84%
that tip of the iceberg in
order to win their approval,

00:37:23.380 --> 00:37:28.420 align:middle line:84%
or I won't be popular,
or they won't like me.

00:37:28.420 --> 00:37:29.520 align:middle line:90%
And so what do we do?

00:37:29.520 --> 00:37:30.930 align:middle line:90%
We shrink ourselves.

00:37:30.930 --> 00:37:33.480 align:middle line:90%
And we make ourselves small.

00:37:33.480 --> 00:37:38.950 align:middle line:84%
And we bring this fear-based
self wherever we go.

00:37:38.950 --> 00:37:42.030 align:middle line:84%
And instead of touching
everybody's lives with love,

00:37:42.030 --> 00:37:46.350 align:middle line:84%
we touch everybody's lives
with fear, because all of us

00:37:46.350 --> 00:37:47.890 align:middle line:90%
are part of a whole.

00:37:47.890 --> 00:37:49.740 align:middle line:84%
So now, here's the
other thing I learned.

00:37:49.740 --> 00:37:52.790 align:middle line:84%
When I say we're
all connected, I

00:37:52.790 --> 00:37:56.570 align:middle line:84%
use the analogy of
fingers on a hand.

00:37:56.570 --> 00:37:59.660 align:middle line:84%
Imagine if each finger
thought they were

00:37:59.660 --> 00:38:03.410 align:middle line:90%
a separate, individual being.

00:38:03.410 --> 00:38:06.620 align:middle line:84%
Each finger thought they were
a separate, individual being.

00:38:06.620 --> 00:38:09.980 align:middle line:84%
And imagine if they
thought, I have

00:38:09.980 --> 00:38:12.123 align:middle line:84%
to get ahead of
these other fingers,

00:38:12.123 --> 00:38:13.790 align:middle line:84%
because there isn't
enough to go around,

00:38:13.790 --> 00:38:15.380 align:middle line:84%
and I have to get
ahead of them, and I

00:38:15.380 --> 00:38:19.190 align:middle line:84%
have to get the job before
they do, or compete with them

00:38:19.190 --> 00:38:20.660 align:middle line:84%
and make more
money than they do.

00:38:20.660 --> 00:38:22.430 align:middle line:84%
And so they're fighting
with each other,

00:38:22.430 --> 00:38:24.740 align:middle line:84%
competing with each other,
trying to get ahead.

00:38:24.740 --> 00:38:27.620 align:middle line:84%
And when they die, they
realize, oh, my gosh, we're

00:38:27.620 --> 00:38:29.480 align:middle line:90%
all part of the same hand.

00:38:29.480 --> 00:38:30.980 align:middle line:84%
If we worked together,
we could have

00:38:30.980 --> 00:38:33.770 align:middle line:84%
gone so much further
and done so much more,

00:38:33.770 --> 00:38:35.000 align:middle line:90%
because we're all one.

00:38:35.000 --> 00:38:35.800 align:middle line:90%
We're one.

00:38:35.800 --> 00:38:41.330 align:middle line:84%
We're part of one entity, one
essence, one consciousness.

00:38:41.330 --> 00:38:45.950 align:middle line:84%
So my consciousness is connected
to yours and yours and yours

00:38:45.950 --> 00:38:47.480 align:middle line:90%
and yours.

00:38:47.480 --> 00:38:51.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's too bad we only
realize this when we die.

00:38:51.440 --> 00:38:54.800 align:middle line:84%
And that was my first question
is, why do we only realize this

00:38:54.800 --> 00:38:55.670 align:middle line:90%
when we die?

00:38:55.670 --> 00:38:59.540 align:middle line:84%
And the answer I got was, no,
we knew it when we were born.

00:38:59.540 --> 00:39:02.210 align:middle line:84%
But it got
conditioned out of us.

00:39:02.210 --> 00:39:05.310 align:middle line:84%
And so each of us
are all connected.

00:39:05.310 --> 00:39:10.010 align:middle line:84%
And so when you
don't love yourself--

00:39:10.010 --> 00:39:12.320 align:middle line:84%
when you don't love
yourself, what happens

00:39:12.320 --> 00:39:16.970 align:middle line:84%
is that space of lack
of love gets taken over

00:39:16.970 --> 00:39:21.200 align:middle line:84%
by fear, because when you
don't love yourself-- so let

00:39:21.200 --> 00:39:23.330 align:middle line:90%
me make it even clearer for you.

00:39:23.330 --> 00:39:26.510 align:middle line:84%
If we are all part
of one consciousness,

00:39:26.510 --> 00:39:32.120 align:middle line:84%
consciousness has chosen to
come here and represent itself

00:39:32.120 --> 00:39:33.110 align:middle line:90%
as all of us.

00:39:33.110 --> 00:39:34.760 align:middle line:90%
And we can call it God.

00:39:34.760 --> 00:39:39.350 align:middle line:84%
God has chosen to come
and express itself

00:39:39.350 --> 00:39:42.020 align:middle line:84%
as you and you and
you and you and me.

00:39:42.020 --> 00:39:49.550 align:middle line:84%
God has chosen to express itself
in all these different forms.

00:39:49.550 --> 00:39:51.620 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness is
expressing itself

00:39:51.620 --> 00:39:54.770 align:middle line:90%
in all these different forms.

00:39:54.770 --> 00:39:59.480 align:middle line:84%
When you love yourself,
you allow God consciousness

00:39:59.480 --> 00:40:04.250 align:middle line:84%
to express itself through you
in the way you were meant to.

00:40:04.250 --> 00:40:08.330 align:middle line:84%
You allow yourself to
be who you truly are.

00:40:08.330 --> 00:40:11.630 align:middle line:84%
When you don't
love yourself, you

00:40:11.630 --> 00:40:15.230 align:middle line:84%
think you are
undeserving and unworthy.

00:40:15.230 --> 00:40:20.480 align:middle line:84%
And so you try to be who
everyone else wants you to be.

00:40:20.480 --> 00:40:23.710 align:middle line:84%
And that's how
you lose yourself.

00:40:23.710 --> 00:40:25.600 align:middle line:90%
That's how you lose yourself.

00:40:25.600 --> 00:40:28.030 align:middle line:84%
That's how we get
into a state of fear--

00:40:28.030 --> 00:40:31.670 align:middle line:84%
a fear of what everyone
else is thinking of us,

00:40:31.670 --> 00:40:33.940 align:middle line:90%
a fear of disappointing people.

00:40:33.940 --> 00:40:35.830 align:middle line:90%
Does anyone relate to that?

00:40:35.830 --> 00:40:37.430 align:middle line:84%
Being in fear of
disappointing people?

00:40:37.430 --> 00:40:38.230 align:middle line:90%
Yep.

00:40:38.230 --> 00:40:41.350 align:middle line:84%
How many of you have
trouble being who you are

00:40:41.350 --> 00:40:44.476 align:middle line:90%
and expressing who you are?

00:40:44.476 --> 00:40:46.550 align:middle line:90%
See, quite a few of you.

00:40:46.550 --> 00:40:49.010 align:middle line:90%
So many people relate to this.

00:40:49.010 --> 00:40:50.590 align:middle line:84%
And if you are an
empath, which I

00:40:50.590 --> 00:40:55.060 align:middle line:84%
gather most people in a
conference like this would be,

00:40:55.060 --> 00:40:57.310 align:middle line:90%
you feel it even more.

00:40:57.310 --> 00:41:01.220 align:middle line:84%
You actually feel the emotions
of other people even more.

00:41:01.220 --> 00:41:05.170 align:middle line:84%
And so it becomes
even more important

00:41:05.170 --> 00:41:08.790 align:middle line:84%
for you to actually love
yourself and find your joy.

00:41:08.790 --> 00:41:09.590 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:41:09.590 --> 00:41:11.680 align:middle line:84%
So what does loving
yourself mean?

00:41:11.680 --> 00:41:17.740 align:middle line:84%
It means finding your joy,
following your passion.

00:41:17.740 --> 00:41:20.350 align:middle line:84%
But here's the hardest
part for people

00:41:20.350 --> 00:41:22.180 align:middle line:90%
who don't love themselves.

00:41:22.180 --> 00:41:23.620 align:middle line:84%
To learn to love
themselves, this

00:41:23.620 --> 00:41:25.780 align:middle line:84%
is the hardest thing
you have to do.

00:41:25.780 --> 00:41:30.490 align:middle line:84%
You have to start
saying no to things that

00:41:30.490 --> 00:41:33.950 align:middle line:90%
no longer feel right to you.

00:41:33.950 --> 00:41:40.340 align:middle line:84%
So many people who
come to my conferences

00:41:40.340 --> 00:41:44.240 align:middle line:84%
and come to conferences and read
books and read my books and so

00:41:44.240 --> 00:41:50.150 align:middle line:84%
on, we all fall into
this trap, where we think

00:41:50.150 --> 00:41:52.340 align:middle line:90%
we need to do more, learn more.

00:41:52.340 --> 00:41:55.520 align:middle line:84%
And when things go wrong in
our life-- when we feel fear,

00:41:55.520 --> 00:41:59.230 align:middle line:84%
we think, oh, my gosh, what do
I need to do to get rid of it?

00:41:59.230 --> 00:42:01.260 align:middle line:90%
What more do I need to learn?

00:42:01.260 --> 00:42:03.650 align:middle line:84%
And we're really judgmental
on ourselves, because we say,

00:42:03.650 --> 00:42:05.483 align:middle line:84%
I'm on this path, I've
read all these books,

00:42:05.483 --> 00:42:06.830 align:middle line:90%
I've been to all these courses.

00:42:06.830 --> 00:42:07.630 align:middle line:90%
What's wrong?

00:42:07.630 --> 00:42:09.380 align:middle line:90%
What am I not getting?

00:42:09.380 --> 00:42:15.560 align:middle line:84%
But in actuality, sometimes we
have to do it the other way.

00:42:15.560 --> 00:42:18.470 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that
we're doing too much.

00:42:18.470 --> 00:42:20.420 align:middle line:84%
The problem is, we're
beating ourselves

00:42:20.420 --> 00:42:22.908 align:middle line:84%
up, thinking that we're
still not getting it.

00:42:22.908 --> 00:42:24.950 align:middle line:84%
We're beating ourselves
up, thinking that there's

00:42:24.950 --> 00:42:27.350 align:middle line:90%
more we have to do and be.

00:42:27.350 --> 00:42:29.300 align:middle line:84%
What if it's the
other way around?

00:42:29.300 --> 00:42:33.560 align:middle line:84%
What if I told you, you
already are everything

00:42:33.560 --> 00:42:35.450 align:middle line:90%
you are trying to attain?

00:42:35.450 --> 00:42:37.800 align:middle line:90%
You already are.

00:42:37.800 --> 00:42:41.930 align:middle line:84%
But you have been convinced,
or convinced to believe,

00:42:41.930 --> 00:42:44.130 align:middle line:84%
that there is something
wrong with you.

00:42:44.130 --> 00:42:48.450 align:middle line:84%
So you are now going out in
search of how to correct it.

00:42:48.450 --> 00:42:52.440 align:middle line:84%
But in actuality, there
is nothing wrong with you.

00:42:52.440 --> 00:42:59.360 align:middle line:84%
And I like to use the
metaphor of Michelangelo.

00:42:59.360 --> 00:43:05.840 align:middle line:84%
Michelangelo used to carve these
beautiful statues of angels--

00:43:05.840 --> 00:43:06.890 align:middle line:90%
beautiful statues.

00:43:06.890 --> 00:43:10.790 align:middle line:84%
And people used to
say to him, how can

00:43:10.790 --> 00:43:13.400 align:middle line:84%
you carve these
beautiful statues

00:43:13.400 --> 00:43:16.760 align:middle line:84%
from these blocks of
marbles without any plans

00:43:16.760 --> 00:43:18.950 align:middle line:84%
or without any
drawings or sketches?

00:43:18.950 --> 00:43:21.350 align:middle line:90%
He just chips away.

00:43:21.350 --> 00:43:22.910 align:middle line:90%
And he carves up an angel.

00:43:22.910 --> 00:43:27.150 align:middle line:84%
And he says, the angel
is already there.

00:43:27.150 --> 00:43:32.120 align:middle line:84%
All I do is chip away at what
is not part of the angel.

00:43:32.120 --> 00:43:35.050 align:middle line:90%
And I set the angel free.

00:43:35.050 --> 00:43:38.530 align:middle line:84%
So what if I was to tell you,
there is nothing more that you

00:43:38.530 --> 00:43:42.460 align:middle line:90%
need to do or be or learn?

00:43:42.460 --> 00:43:44.510 align:middle line:90%
But it's the opposite.

00:43:44.510 --> 00:43:48.370 align:middle line:84%
You need to let go
of what is not you.

00:43:48.370 --> 00:43:53.620 align:middle line:84%
Chip away at what is not
you, and set that angel free.

00:43:53.620 --> 00:43:55.420 align:middle line:90%
Set your heart free.

00:43:55.420 --> 00:43:57.230 align:middle line:90%
Set your soul free.

00:43:57.230 --> 00:44:00.310 align:middle line:84%
That's what your soul is
really crying out for.

00:44:00.310 --> 00:44:06.970 align:middle line:84%
And the way I do that is, we
start by saying things like,

00:44:06.970 --> 00:44:09.780 align:middle line:84%
where have I said
"yes" when I mean "no"?

00:44:09.780 --> 00:44:12.430 align:middle line:84%
And I've said "yes" for the
wrong reasons, because I'm

00:44:12.430 --> 00:44:14.870 align:middle line:90%
afraid of disappointing people.

00:44:14.870 --> 00:44:19.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid of what people
think of me, because that's

00:44:19.150 --> 00:44:21.265 align:middle line:84%
one way that we add
all these layers.

00:44:21.265 --> 00:44:26.890 align:middle line:90%


00:44:26.890 --> 00:44:34.310 align:middle line:84%
The other thing is, what have
I taken on that's not mine?

00:44:34.310 --> 00:44:39.020 align:middle line:84%
What have I taken
on that's not mine?

00:44:39.020 --> 00:44:42.600 align:middle line:84%
Am I doing things
for other people?

00:44:42.600 --> 00:44:46.710 align:middle line:84%
Or am I getting into dramas
that are not my dramas,

00:44:46.710 --> 00:44:48.240 align:middle line:90%
into other people's fears?

00:44:48.240 --> 00:44:49.040 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:44:49.040 --> 00:44:53.230 align:middle line:84%
So here's where you get drawn
in really, really easily.

00:44:53.230 --> 00:44:54.920 align:middle line:90%
And we're in this climate--

00:44:54.920 --> 00:44:57.210 align:middle line:84%
when I say "this
climate," about the things

00:44:57.210 --> 00:44:59.550 align:middle line:84%
that are going on in
the world right now.

00:44:59.550 --> 00:45:04.260 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of things
that feel scary and dark.

00:45:04.260 --> 00:45:06.360 align:middle line:84%
And you get drawn
in, because people

00:45:06.360 --> 00:45:12.060 align:middle line:84%
make you feel guilty that
you have to be in this--

00:45:12.060 --> 00:45:15.840 align:middle line:84%
maybe a campaign that makes
you feel angry or makes

00:45:15.840 --> 00:45:19.110 align:middle line:84%
you research things that
makes you feel really angry

00:45:19.110 --> 00:45:21.270 align:middle line:90%
and makes you feel fearful.

00:45:21.270 --> 00:45:26.020 align:middle line:84%
Or even our medical system
comes from a fear-based place.

00:45:26.020 --> 00:45:30.330 align:middle line:84%
Our medical system is focused
on looking for illness.

00:45:30.330 --> 00:45:33.150 align:middle line:90%
It's not focused on wellness.

00:45:33.150 --> 00:45:36.900 align:middle line:84%
It's focused on
looking for illness.

00:45:36.900 --> 00:45:40.050 align:middle line:84%
So all these things are always
focused on the darkness.

00:45:40.050 --> 00:45:44.320 align:middle line:84%
What I always say is that,
especially in this world

00:45:44.320 --> 00:45:45.120 align:middle line:90%
right now--

00:45:45.120 --> 00:45:47.520 align:middle line:90%
the climate the way it is--

00:45:47.520 --> 00:45:52.620 align:middle line:84%
it's really important that
you focus on your light.

00:45:52.620 --> 00:45:56.070 align:middle line:84%
And don't allow
people, using guilt,

00:45:56.070 --> 00:45:59.610 align:middle line:84%
or you trying to please people,
and people who have dramas,

00:45:59.610 --> 00:46:02.580 align:middle line:84%
or people who are involved in
things that you don't like--

00:46:02.580 --> 00:46:05.400 align:middle line:90%
don't allow them to draw you in.

00:46:05.400 --> 00:46:09.990 align:middle line:84%
You are not helping people by
stepping into the darkness.

00:46:09.990 --> 00:46:14.190 align:middle line:84%
You help people by
holding onto the light.

00:46:14.190 --> 00:46:15.900 align:middle line:90%
And don't feel guilty about it.

00:46:15.900 --> 00:46:18.040 align:middle line:90%
That's super important.

00:46:18.040 --> 00:46:20.460 align:middle line:84%
So now, the other thing
is, let's talk a little bit

00:46:20.460 --> 00:46:22.320 align:middle line:90%
about illness.

00:46:22.320 --> 00:46:27.390 align:middle line:84%
And I want to also share a
little bit of a meditation

00:46:27.390 --> 00:46:31.140 align:middle line:84%
with you, because I've created
a new meditation, taking people

00:46:31.140 --> 00:46:33.520 align:middle line:84%
into their own
near-death experience.

00:46:33.520 --> 00:46:35.770 align:middle line:84%
But what I wanted to
do is share a 10--

00:46:35.770 --> 00:46:36.570 align:middle line:90%
live.

00:46:36.570 --> 00:46:37.920 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do this live--

00:46:37.920 --> 00:46:41.010 align:middle line:84%
share a 10 or 15-minute
sample with you.

00:46:41.010 --> 00:46:42.450 align:middle line:90%
And then-- bless you.

00:46:42.450 --> 00:46:45.390 align:middle line:84%
And then we can go into
a couple of questions,

00:46:45.390 --> 00:46:47.740 align:middle line:90%
if there's time at the end.

00:46:47.740 --> 00:46:51.520 align:middle line:90%
So a little bit about illness--

00:46:51.520 --> 00:46:54.030 align:middle line:84%
your body is much
smarter than you think.

00:46:54.030 --> 00:46:56.280 align:middle line:84%
Your body is capable
of so much more

00:46:56.280 --> 00:46:58.020 align:middle line:90%
than you've been led to believe.

00:46:58.020 --> 00:47:01.620 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately,
our medical system

00:47:01.620 --> 00:47:06.150 align:middle line:84%
is fear-focused, as opposed
to love or health-focused.

00:47:06.150 --> 00:47:07.800 align:middle line:90%
Unfortunately, this is the case.

00:47:07.800 --> 00:47:10.620 align:middle line:84%
If it were up to
me, I would actually

00:47:10.620 --> 00:47:16.170 align:middle line:84%
